Count.reads.InBins = function(mark.BAM, regions, spike = 1, binsize = 1, field = "score"){
    #Spike-in normalize the BAMs
    #mark.BAM$count = mark.BAM$count / spike;
    #Resize each read from BAM to 1bp (center position of each read)
    mark.BAM.res = resize(mark.BAM, width = 1, fix = "center");
    #Compute coverage
    mark.BAM.res = GRanges(coverage(mark.BAM.res, weight="count"));
    mark.BAM.res = makeGRangesBRG(mark.BAM.res[mark.BAM.res$score > 0]);

    #Count DHS signal within each CTCF peak
    mark.BAM.score = getCountsByPositions(mark.BAM.res, regions, binsize = binsize, field="score");
    
    return(mark.BAM.score/spike)
}

getMatrixQuantiles = function( mat, nquantiles, FUN="sum" ) {
    #Import required libraries
    library(iterators)
    library(foreach)
    
    #Approx. the how many rows fall within each quantile --> chunksize = nr nows in each quantile
    chunksize = floor( nrow(mat)/nquantiles );
    #For each chunksize, sum up the values in each colum and rbind it as a new row 
    y = foreach( i=iter(mat, by='row', chunksize=chunksize), .combine='rbind' ) %do% {
        #"2" = apply FUN to columns ("1" would be rows)
        return(apply(i, 2, FUN=FUN));
    };
    return(y[1:nquantiles,]);
}

#8. Avoid taking into account regions with high DHS scores: regions at the TSS (high MNase cutting efficiency)
    CTCF_peaks.bp = resize(CTCF_peaks, width = 1, fix = "center");
    CTCF_peaks.bp.toRemove = CTCF_peaks.bp + 1000;

    #Resize each CTCF peaks to 1-bp start position & 1-bp end position of each peak
    CTCF_peaks.bp.plus5kb = resize(CTCF_peaks.bp.toRemove, width=1, fix="end");
    CTCF_peaks.bp.minus5kb = resize(CTCF_peaks.bp.toRemove, width=1, fix="start");

    #Take regions adjacent to the 4kb TSS: meaning, take 10kb in each direction from the CTCF center position & avoid 4kb around TSS
    CTCF_peaks.bp.minus5kb = promoters(CTCF_peaks.bp.minus5kb, upstream=10000, downstream=0)
    CTCF_peaks.bp.plus5kb = promoters(CTCF_peaks.bp.plus5kb, upstream=0, downstream=10000)

    #Merge the 2 regions
    CTCF_peaks.K4me1 = c(CTCF_peaks.bp.plus5kb, CTCF_peaks.bp.minus5kb);

Count.reads.InBins = function(mark.BAM, regions, spike = 1, binsize = 1, field = "score"){
    #Spike-in normalize the BAMs
    #mark.BAM$count = mark.BAM$count / spike;
    #Resize each read from BAM to 1bp (center position of each read)
    mark.BAM.res = resize(mark.BAM, width = 1, fix = "center");
    #Compute coverage
    mark.BAM.res = GRanges(coverage(mark.BAM.res, weight="count"));
    mark.BAM.res = makeGRangesBRG(mark.BAM.res[mark.BAM.res$score > 0]);

    #Count DHS signal within each CTCF peak
    mark.BAM.score = getCountsByPositions(mark.BAM.res, regions, binsize = binsize, field="score");
    
    return(mark.BAM.score/spike)
}

getMatrixQuantiles = function( mat, nquantiles, FUN="sum" ) {
    #Import required libraries
    library(iterators)
    library(foreach)
    
    #Approx. the how many rows fall within each quantile --> chunksize = nr nows in each quantile
    chunksize = floor( nrow(mat)/nquantiles );
    #For each chunksize, sum up the values in each colum and rbind it as a new row 
    y = foreach( i=iter(mat, by='row', chunksize=chunksize), .combine='rbind' ) %do% {
        #"2" = apply FUN to columns ("1" would be rows)
        return(apply(i, 2, FUN=FUN));
    };
    return(y[1:nquantiles,]);
}

Count.reads.InBins = function(mark.BAM, regions, spike = 1, binsize = 1, field = "score"){
    #Spike-in normalize the BAMs
    #mark.BAM$count = mark.BAM$count / spike;
    #Resize each read from BAM to 1bp (center position of each read)
    mark.BAM.res = resize(mark.BAM, width = 1, fix = "center");
    #Compute coverage
    mark.BAM.res = GRanges(coverage(mark.BAM.res, weight="count"));
    mark.BAM.res = makeGRangesBRG(mark.BAM.res[mark.BAM.res$score > 0]);

    #Count DHS signal within each CTCF peak
    mark.BAM.score = getCountsByPositions(mark.BAM.res, regions, binsize = binsize, field="score");
    
    return(mark.BAM.score/spike)
}

getMatrixQuantiles = function( mat, nquantiles, FUN="sum" ) {
    #Import required libraries
    library(iterators)
    library(foreach)
    
    #Approx. the how many rows fall within each quantile --> chunksize = nr nows in each quantile
    chunksize = floor( nrow(mat)/nquantiles );
    #For each chunksize, sum up the values in each colum and rbind it as a new row 
    y = foreach( i=iter(mat, by='row', chunksize=chunksize), .combine='rbind' ) %do% {
        #"2" = apply FUN to columns ("1" would be rows)
        return(apply(i, 2, FUN=FUN));
    };
    return(y[1:nquantiles,]);
}

Count.reads.InBins = function(mark.BAM, regions, spike = 1, binsize = 1, field = "score"){
    #Spike-in normalize the BAMs
    #mark.BAM$count = mark.BAM$count / spike;
    #Resize each read from BAM to 1bp (center position of each read)
    mark.BAM.res = resize(mark.BAM, width = 1, fix = "center");
    #Compute coverage
    mark.BAM.res = GRanges(coverage(mark.BAM.res, weight="count"));
    mark.BAM.res = makeGRangesBRG(mark.BAM.res[mark.BAM.res$score > 0]);

    #Count DHS signal within each CTCF peak
    mark.BAM.score = getCountsByPositions(mark.BAM.res, regions, binsize = binsize, field="score");
    
    return(mark.BAM.score/spike)
}

getMatrixQuantiles = function( mat, nquantiles, FUN="sum" ) {
    #Import required libraries
    library(iterators)
    library(foreach)
    
    #Approx. the how many rows fall within each quantile --> chunksize = nr nows in each quantile
    chunksize = floor( nrow(mat)/nquantiles );
    #For each chunksize, sum up the values in each colum and rbind it as a new row 
    y = foreach( i=iter(mat, by='row', chunksize=chunksize), .combine='rbind' ) %do% {
        #"2" = apply FUN to columns ("1" would be rows)
        return(apply(i, 2, FUN=FUN));
    };
    return(y[1:nquantiles,]);
}

Count.reads.InBins = function(mark.BAM, regions, spike = 1, binsize = 1, field = "score"){
    #Spike-in normalize the BAMs
    #mark.BAM$count = mark.BAM$count / spike;
    #Resize each read from BAM to 1bp (center position of each read)
    mark.BAM.res = resize(mark.BAM, width = 1, fix = "center");
    #Compute coverage
    mark.BAM.res = GRanges(coverage(mark.BAM.res, weight="count"));
    mark.BAM.res = makeGRangesBRG(mark.BAM.res[mark.BAM.res$score > 0]);

    #Count DHS signal within each CTCF peak
    mark.BAM.score = getCountsByPositions(mark.BAM.res, regions, binsize = binsize, field="score");
    
    return(mark.BAM.score/spike)
}

Count.reads.InBins = function(mark.BAM, regions, spike = 1, binsize = 1, field = "score"){
    #Spike-in normalize the BAMs
    #mark.BAM$count = mark.BAM$count / spike;
    #Resize each read from BAM to 1bp (center position of each read)
    mark.BAM.res = resize(mark.BAM, width = 1, fix = "center");
    #Compute coverage
    mark.BAM.res = GRanges(coverage(mark.BAM.res, weight="count"));
    mark.BAM.res = makeGRangesBRG(mark.BAM.res[mark.BAM.res$score > 0]);

    #Count DHS signal within each CTCF peak
    mark.BAM.score = getCountsByPositions(mark.BAM.res, regions, binsize = binsize, field="score");
    
    return(mark.BAM.score/spike)
}

getMatrixQuantiles = function( mat, nquantiles, FUN="sum" ) {
    #Import required libraries
    library(iterators)
    library(foreach)
    
    #Approx. the how many rows fall within each quantile --> chunksize = nr nows in each quantile
    chunksize = floor( nrow(mat)/nquantiles );
    #For each chunksize, sum up the values in each colum and rbind it as a new row 
    y = foreach( i=iter(mat, by='row', chunksize=chunksize), .combine='rbind' ) %do% {
        #"2" = apply FUN to columns ("1" would be rows)
        return(apply(i, 2, FUN=FUN));
    };
    return(y[1:nquantiles,]);
}
